The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning-based algorithm for load balancing in ultra-dense networks. This involves the use of machine learning techniques to optimize network performance, which falls under the categories of network optimization (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT).
